 Bradley Keoun  in New York at 
 bkeoun@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                           
                 
                 
                                       
                                   
               
                        
           
                          July 1 (Bloomberg) -- The U.S. Treasury Department sold 1.1 billion Citigroup Inc. shares since May 26, cutting its stake in the U.S. lender to 18 percent. Sales to date, including a sale earlier this year of 1.5 billion shares, have produced a total of $10.5 billion of proceeds, according to a Treasury statement today. Bloomberg's Peter Cook reports. (Source: Bloomberg)  
                           

     
